# Gauge.U1

U(1) gauge algebra.

The U(1) gauge algebra is the abelian Lie algebra u(1) ≅ ℝ, with the compact
Lie group U(1) = {e^{iθ} : θ ∈ ℝ} as its associated group.

In the Standard Model, U(1)_Y is the hypercharge gauge factor.
The generator is the hypercharge Y, with electric charge:
  Q = T₃ + Y/2  (or Q = T₃ + Y, depending on hypercharge normalization)

Convention: hypercharge normalization follows the Standard Model with
  Q = T₃ + Y/2  and Y values as in the GUT-normalized convention.
  This choice is recorded explicitly; other conventions are possible.

Status: stub.
-/

